inn1.comm: Two slips in place. Full and straight, pushed down to mid-on
moves in to the middle stump, full in length, Hafeez taps it to mid-on
drifts to the middle and leg line, flicked away to deep square-leg region
in the zone outside off, left alone
straightens outside off stump, from a full length, left alone
fuller, on the middle, flicked uppishly but short of midwicket
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
tilts in from outside off, full in length, pushed to the off side

Caught at second slip! There has been no major seam movement so far and even this delivery just straightens. It landed on a good length outside off and straightened, Shehzad wafted away from the body and got a thick edge
tilts in from outside off, Kamran decides to shoulder arms and the ball rushes past the off stump
full in length, on the middle, Kamran stays at his crease and taps the ball behind square-leg
gets back to punch this short-of-length delivery to backward point
Top shot! It was a short-of-length delivery just outside off, Kamran shifted his weight back and punched it on the up and through point.
stays back to push this out to covers
moves in from outside off, Kamran defends it close on the off side
full in length on the off stump line, Kamran is a touch late in getting forward but eventually does so to stab this one to the on side. He got a inside edge on to his right boot
stays back to push this to backward point
taps this one to cover point for a single

Dragged on! It landed short of length outside off stump and moved back in a bit. Nothing alarming, just a little bit. Akmal saw the width and shaped for his punchy forcing shot through the off side. Did the ball stop on him a touch? He seemed to have pushed at it early, and the bat came down in an angle,  and got a fatal inside edge. The leg stump is pegged back. He wasn't in great position to play that shot.
stays back to defend to the off side
pushed to the off side, towards gully, for a single
leans forward to defend to the on side of the pitch
in the corridor outside off, left alone
taps this to point region for a single
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
banged in short of length, mistimes the pull to square-leg
fuller in length, just outside off, Hafeez leans forward and across to defend
leans forward to push this to short cover
gets back to defend this short-of-length delivery back down the pitch
banged in short and Hafeez swivels back to pull it through midwicket for three runs
Crack! Another one banged in short and Hafeez plays a cracking pull shot over square-leg to collect a boundary
Not sure what's the bowling plan is here. Yet another one dragged in short and Hafeez pulls it to the midwicket boundary. Whack!
fuller in length and its been defended to the off side
leans across, covers the off stump and shoulders arms
gets back to defend this back to the bowler
fuller and outside off, left alone
A well-directed bouncer on the off stump line and Younis, who was looking to get on the front foot, is surprised and hops to fend it to the off
works this past square-leg
in the corridor outside off stump, left alone
full in length outside off, Hafeez leans forward and across to tap to backward point
drives to left of mid-off where Oram stops and fires a throw.. Younis Khan dives to get back inside the crease. The throw didn't find the stumps btw
stays back to push to the off side
starts off with a bad delivery - short and on the leg stump line, Hafeez pulls it away to the backward square-leg boundary
drifts to the hips, tucked to short fine-leg fielder
Smack! Bennett bowls a full length delivery on the middle. Blink. Whack. The ball sails over long-on. Hafeez had cleared his front foot and thwacked it through the line
works this wide of mid-on for a single

edged but does it carry? It straightens outside off stump and Younis got an edge. McCullum tried to lunge forward and scoop it but the ball seems to have bounced just before the gloves. The third umpire says Not out. McCullum said he wasn't sure whether it had carried.
full delivery on the off and middle, pushed to mid-on
on the middle stump line, tapped to right of square-leg
leans forward to push it past the bowler
lands full in length outside off and straightens, left alone
gets close to the short-of-the-length delivery to punch it through cover point. Fab strike.
full in length outside off, left alone
kicks up from back of length, defended to the on side
almost yorker length, pushed out towards mid-on
gets behind the line of the full-length delivery on the middle stump line and defends to the off
short in length outside off, Younis punches it to left of backward point
sprays to the pads, flicked to deep square-leg region
gets back, bends his knees, gets into position for the punchy drive through point
homing on the off stump, tapped close to the off and they rush across
yorker length delivery, dug out to the on side of the pitch. Brendon loved that delivery
leans forward to flick uppishly but to the right of the diving Styris at short midwicket. He almost caught that one. I reckon it brushed his fingers as it flew away from him
gets forward to defend
in the corridor outside off stump, left alone
stays back to defend the short of length delivery to covers
kicks up outside off stump, stabbed to the off side
on a length outside off, tapped to backward point
short of a good length on leg stump, tucked away into the leg side, off the thigh, just the single
driven on the up, lands on a good length and it's caressed through that gap between point and cover for a boundary
in the channel outside off, tapped towards cover off the front foot
goodish length on middle, gets forward and tapped into the off side
angling in towards the off stump, 123 kmph, dropping in pace here, defended into the off side
drawing him forward with that good length delivery outside off, Younis reaches forward and pushes it to extra cover
back of a length on middle, rocks back and drops it in front of cover
good length on the off, taps it towards cover off the front foot
short of a good length on middle and leg, punched past midwicket
banged in short and it's down the leg side, attempted bouncer gone wrong, called a wide
eased off the front foot between mid-off and extra cover for a single
short of a good length outside off, run down to third man for a single
slower one this time, trying the offcutter, pushed back past Southee who dives full length to his right but can't get his hand to it
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and turns it towards midwicket
short, these have been punished today, pulled away this time as well but there is a deep square leg in place

gone! What was Younis doing there? He appeared to have made his mind up there, came down the track before it was delivered and failed to pick the change in pace, it was the slower one, went through with his attempted loft over mid-on, mistimed and was caught comfortably
taps it to left of short cover, wants a single but decides to get back
left alone and it bounces once before it reaches the keeper. It was the slower off cutter
drags this short and he goes for the short-arm pull over midwicket. Neatly done. The white ball flies away to the boundary
gets forward to tap it to the off side, they think about a run but kill the thought
goes for the off cutter but sprays it wide outside off. Not given wide, though. Hmmm
this one kicks up outside off, run down to third man
just outside the off stump, tapped to point
the slower bouncer, Hafeez adjusted to the lack of pace and dragged it to the deep backward square-leg region
full and outside off stump, left alone
stays back to defend this slowish delivery to the off
lands full in length outside off, defended to the off
slower one, on the off, worked to short midwicket
just outside off stump, Hafeez seemed cramped for room as he shaped to cut but he adjusted to run it through the vacant slip region .. good fielding by the third man
drifts to the pads this time and Hafeez shuffles inside the line and unfurls the leg glance to perfection. Nicely done.
better delivery: on the off and middle, full in length, extra bounce and perhaps it stopped a touch on Hafeez who adjusted by taking out the bottom-hand of the handle and pushing it to the off
short in length, Misbah gets back to punch it to point
leans forward to drive and edges it, along the ground, to first slip
gets behind the line to defend to covers
fullish, on the legs, flicked behind square-leg for a single
leans across to square drive it through point
leans forward to drive to mid-on
gets back to steer this to point
fuller, Hafeez glides forward to flick it down to fine-leg region
shorter in length, Misbah stays back to work it past square-leg

almost caught by Brendon. It was full in length outside off stump and straightened; Hafeez stabbed inside the line and it went of the outside edge. Brendon dived full stretch to his right, and got his right hand to it even as the ball was dying on him but couldn't hold on.
leans forward to defend this
gets forward to run this down to third man for a single
fullish and drifting down the leg side, Brendon dives but is unable to cut it off. It's fielded near the boundary.. 1 wide + 3 runs
flicks this to the on side for a single
Crunchy! Hafeez has been really fluent today. He leaned forward and across to cream this through covers
from wide of the crease, comes in from a good length, pushed out to point
gets forward to defend to the on side
full and on the legs, flicked away behind square-leg
flighted on the leg stump line, from round the stumps, turned past square-leg
from wide of the crease, down the leg side..
paddles this one down to fine-leg region for a single
floated around the leg and middle line, slow, Hafeez tries to dab it to the on side but is beaten by the lack of the pace and is hit on the pad. Going down leg
on the middle stump line, deflected to short midwicket
keeps a touch low outside off, cut away to deep backward point
cuts in from outside off, steered to left of backward point for a single
on the off stump line, full, jabbed to backward point
on the middle stump line, wristed behind square-leg for a single
in the channel outside off, left alone
stays back to push it out to the off side
leans forward to defend it back down the pitch
lands full in length around off and turns away, defended to the off
fuller, on the middle, whipped away to short midwicket
on the pads, turned down to short fine-leg region
on the middle stump line, drifts in and then turns, dabbed to the on side
loopy delivery outside off, chopped to backward point
gets back to cut to deep point
short in length, just outside off, dabbed to backward point
full and in the zone outside off, left alone
banged in short, goes for the pull and mistimes it but clears midwicket
leans forward to defend this to the on side
in the zone outside off, nudged to backward point
full in length, on the middle, worked behind square-leg
leans well forward to nudge to the on side
paddle sweep to backward square-leg fielder
drifts in from round the stumps, full in length around off and turns away, defended to the off

Stumping chance missed Oh what a mess by Brendon. Woodcock holds his head in agony. He has bowled well so far. It drifted in and Misbah charged out for the big hit. But the ball dipped and turned away past the desperate lunge but McCullum makes a complete mess. He doesn't even collect it
gets forward to defend to the on side
presses back to punch it through mid-on
stays back to chop it down to third man
stays back to steer this to third man for a single
short in length outside off, cut down to third man
on the middle, dabbed behind square-leg
slower off cutter outside off, Misbah defends to the off
the slow bouncer, Misbah had to wait for the ball to arrive before he lapped it around the corner
loopy delivery from round the stumps, pushed to covers
moves outside leg, Woodcock flights in on the middle stump line, Misbah leans across to defend
stays back to punch this to long-on
floated full and drifting outside leg stump and Hafeez drag-sweeps it over backward square-leg fielder
on the middle and leg, flighted on a good length, nudged back down the track
a tad quicker ,on the middle, squeezed to short midwicket
on the middle stump line, the slow off cutter, worked past backward square-leg fielder
another slower off cutter, full, worked past square-leg
leans forward to dab this to the on side
another off cutter... lbw shout as Misbah plays all around it. Styris stands and stares at the umpire. The point of impact was perhaps just outside the off stump.
works this from the middle stump line to deep backward square-leg region. 50 of the partnership
yet another slow off cutter, full, deflected to midwicket
full delivery, paddled away to fine-leg region
slows up the pace, outside off, cut away to deep point
pushes right back to force this down to long-on
Flighted on a good length on the middle and Hafeez stretches forward to play a lovely flamboyant skillful lofted drive over the bowler
quicker one outside off, steered to short third man
flighted full outside off, sweeps it to deep midwicket
almost drifts away this off cutter ... Hafeez leans forward to push it to covers
on the off and middle line, pushed down to long-on. Direct hit from woodcock but the batsman was in
leans forward to work this to square-leg
on the middle and leg, wristed to deep backward square-leg
on the middle and off line, pushed back to the bowler
fuller, around off stump, driven back to Styris
gets well back to defend to the on side
flighted outside off, Misbah goes for the slog sweep and ends up dragging it to square-leg fielder
backs away and cuts to deep point region
quicker, shorter, cut to deep point again
Misbah has begun to take some risks now. He moves outside leg before the release and goes for a big slog sweep but ends up mistiming it to deep midwicket
outside off stump, steered to deep point
leans forward to on drive for a single
fetched this from the off and middle line and whipped it to deep square-leg region
leans forward to drive to the off side
Boom! Long hop from Styris and Misbah rocks back to pull it away to the square-leg boundary
moves outside leg and moves back in and steers to cover point for a single. Guptill with the throw but it gets stuck in his palm and the release goes awry. Crowd laugh
fetches it from outside off and plays the paddle sweep and top edges it but wide of the backward square-leg fielder
presses back to punch it to the off
slightly short in length, cut away to deep point
moves outside the leg stump, Woodcock follows him, tapped past square-leg
flighted on the leg and middle, glanced away for a single
backs away outside leg and cuts it to deep point
floated outside leg, on a good length ,swept away for a single
leans forward to push to cover point for a single
the slow off cutter, short in length, pulled away to deep backward square-leg fielder. Misbah is upset with himself for missing out on an opportunity to pull it away for a boundary
leans forward to on drive for a single
full in length, on the middle, worked behind square-leg
yet another slow off cutter from Styris, pushed to the off
gets forward to nudge this to short midwicket
flighted full in length, on the middle and leg, some extra bounce, stabbed to the on side
moves outside leg and goes for a big slog sweep but fails to connect. It goes past the leg stump, McCullum doesn't collect cleanly but Misbah's back leg was inside the crease
leans forward to steer to point
just outside off, guided to short third man
stays back to cut to deep backward point
flighted on the leg stump line, whipped to deep midwicket
angling in, on a good length on middle, pushed back to the bowler
goes after that, lands on a length and he swings it wide of deep midwicket, didn't quite get hold of it though
short of a good length on middle, defended back to the bowler
fullish outside off, eased towards deep point for a single
goodish length, in the channel outside off, pushed towards extra cover
short ball bowled down the leg side, goes for the pull, doesn't connect, called a wide
back of a length on middle, rocks back and punches it to the bowler
a bit of width there, lands on a length, steered towards point
slower ball on the pads, tries to tickle it square, clips the pads, they sneak a leg bye
Misbah had shaped up for an expansive shot but adjusted well to the length, rocking back to punch it into the leg side for a single
lovely hit, safe shot, landed on a good length, mid-off was up and he sensed a chance, rocked forward and smacked it over the in-field
angling towards middle, gets across to play it to midwicket
Misbah falls, trying to force the pace. He went down the track and tried to clear  the length delivery over mid-off but didn't connect well. Styris pouches it at mid-off
stays back to defend to the off side of the pitch
gets forward to tap it to mid-on
short in length around off stump, dabbed towards point
straightens outside off, run down to third man
full in length, around off, driven to mid-off
shuffles to off stump line and steers this to backward point
full in length, tilting in towards the off stump, pushed out to covers
shuffles across and goes for the big hit down the ground but ends up slicing it over wide mid-off. Thick edge but the wind carries it safely beyond mid-off
slower one, on a good length, punched down to long-on for a single
stays back to guide this down to third man
taps it towards backward point, wants a single but Hafeez asks him to get back
short in length outside off, run down to third man
Bosh! He shuffled towards off, then cleared the front foot and pulled the short delivery over midwicket boundary. Smashed!
fuller, outside off, slashed to third man
leans forward to defend the good-length delivery to backward point
slower one outside off, steered straight to backward point
runs this down to third man to retain the strike.
preses back to punch this to short extra cover
on the middle, pushed back to the bowler

on the leg and middle line, dabbed wide of short midwicket and almost a mixup between the two batsmen but Hafeez gets back in time. He then has a look at his partner and walks to the middle of the pitch to have a chat
flicks this wide of midwicket for a single
quicker, on the off, punched down to long-on
rocks back to cut to deep point region
gets back and across to cut it down to third man
in the zone outside off, Hafeez shifts his weight back and steers it wide of backward point
shuffles across, reaches outside off and paddles it away behind square-leg! It was a slower one
on the off stump line, cut away to backward point
fuller, on the middle, deflected to short midwicket
slower, short in length on the middle, dabbed behind square-leg for a single
flighted on the leg and middle, eased to long-on, past the diving bowler
rushes down the track and blasts this to the left of the long-off. He hit that  really hard
Woodcock drags this one short and Umar rocks back, opens the front foot and swings it to the wide midwicket boundary
worked behind square-leg for a single

That's his maiden hundred He brought it up with a cut to deep point region. He looks up to the skies. Pakistan flags go up around the arena. The dressing room is happy. He holds his arms aloft. Kamran Akmal screams in delight from the dressing room.
presses back to force it down to long-on
fullish, on the middle and leg, squeezed past square-leg
really full again, dug out to the on side of the pitch
another yorker length, dug out to just outside the popping crease .. they rush across for the run. Southee too charges down the pitch and dives to pick the ball but doesn't collect in time
moves outside leg, fullish delivery arrives, he goes for the big hit but edges it to fine-leg region
Low dipping full toss, attempted yorker it was, Hafeez leaned across to paddle it to the fine-leg boundary. Bit of an edge
moves outside leg and scythes this one in the air and to the right of mid-off. Blasted it!
gets away from the leg stump, a full delivery arrives, Umar tries to slash it to the off side but the bottom-hand comes off the handle and he ends up slicing the ball to point
slower one around off, mistimed to extra cover
Massive! It was the slower one, on a good length around off, Hafeez cleared the front foot and heaved it over wide long-on!

Fine knock comes to an end. It was the low full toss and Hafeez tries to whip it over the on side field but top edges it to the on side. Rosco, at midwicket, moves to his left to take it. Good knock from Hafeez. His maiden ton. Just ahead of the WC. Purrfect timing.
low full toss again, this time on the leg stump line, and Umar flays it over deep backward square-leg region
this one is outside off stump and Umar tries to run it down to third man and gets a profitable edge through vacant slip. Runs coming in at a flood here for Pakistan.
leans forward to on drive this for a single
moves outside leg and drives to mid-off for a single
another low full toss, swatted away to deep midwicket
low dipping full toss around the off stump and Umar off drives it to left of mid-off to collect another boundary.
this one lands, just short of the blockhole, squeezed to backward point
More full tosses arrive. This one has been whipped to deep midwicket
the slower one now, dragged down to deep square-leg region
Thump! Afridi clears his front foot and heaves this high, really high, but also manages to clear wide long-on
gets forward to whip this full delivery to wide midwicket region
Thunderous wallop! Afridi moves outside leg and Oram bangs it in short. Afridi adjusts and crash-pulls it over wide midwicket boundary, into the stands

Nasty beamer! Oram apologises. The ball must have slipped out of the hand.  It was the full toss around the right shoulder, Afridi was looking to swing it to the on side and is hit on the right shoulder. He is in pain. He gets up to see Oram next to him and Afridi wraps his arms around Oram to sort of say, it's all right mate.
Whackity whack! He moves outside leg and slices this over the off-side field. To the cover boundary. What a run fest these last few overs have been.
moves down the track and whips it through midwicket
runs this past square-leg for a single
low full toss on the middle - the full tosses keep coming- whipped away to deep midwicket
Six over fine-leg! Supah! It was yet another full toss and Shahid paddled it up and over fine-leg! That bottom-hand again.
dropped by Bennett at short third man. Afridi moved outside leg, Southee hurled another full toss, Afridi went for the big hit but ended up slicing it to Bennett who drops it. What a clanger!
moves outside leg, the bowler follows him, whipped to midwicket
full delivery, hit past midwicket for a single
slower one, on a good length around off, Afridi goes for a big heave-ho and edges it to short fine-leg region
clears the front foot and drives this good-length delivery to long-on
Whaddaplayaaa! He makes it look simple. Just clear the front foot, hold your balance and swing through the line. This one sails over the straight boundary.
This is amazing! Six over cover point! It was the short delivery and Shahid Afridi whacks it up and over cover point. Blast!
fuller, straighter driven to long-on. 50 from 19 deliveries. Equals the quickest fifty in New Zealand. Brendon's record. Insane fun!

shuffles across to outside off and tries to paddle it but misses. The off stump is pegged back. Good hand from Umar, though. Pakistan look so good when the top order gives them a solid base and the dangerous men lurking in the lower order are given a free licence to hit. That's how they played in 80's. And they continue to do it in some style even now
Carved! He reaches outside off and carves the full delivery to right of sweeper cover where Oram makes a sliding stop.
Violence! The full tosses keep coming from NZ and they keep disappearing. Afridi has smashed this to wide long-off boundary.
another full toss but this dips rapidly on Afridi who makes contact with the toe end of the bat, a single to sweeper cover
shoves this towards long-off for a single
Crash Boom Blast. The Afridi way. It's a full delivery. Blink. The ball is being thrown back from the straight boundary. He drilled that
The fun continues. Shahid Afridi has picked this slower bouncer, waited on it before pulling it to the square-leg boundary
moves outside leg and edges the whippy shot to fine-leg

Fine catch from Brendon. It was the good-length delivery cutting into Afridi who went for the pull but got an inside edge. Baz dives to his left to pluck it with his left hand. Murderous innings from Afridi ends. It was immense fun to watch.
pushed down towards mid-on for a single
fullish delivery on the middle, heaved away to deep midwicket
low inswinging full toss, Wahab goes for the big hit and misses it. The ball rolls away of his pad
low full toss again, driven to left of mid-off and Wahab pushes hard and turns back for the second run.

inn2.comm: full in length, pushed down to mid-off
drops this short and Guptill unfurls the short-arm pull to the midwicket boundary
fuller in length, worked to short midwicket
length delivery that straightens outside off, punched down to mid-off
on the off and middle line, tapped towards mid-off
gets back to punch it firmly to short extra cover
from a short run-up, drifts to the pads and Jamie How whips it away to backward square-leg boundary.
More runs. Fullish on the leg and middle line, worked through midwicket for couple of runs
short in length, straightens on the middle and leg, tapped wide of midwicket
fuller, on the middle and leg, turned straight to midwicket. He would feel he missed out on an opportunity to collect a four there
finally, one in the off-stump channel, angling across, left alone
back to the leg-stump line, he tries to whip it over square-leg, mises and is struck on the pad
full in length, just outside off stump, Jamie leans forward to defend
gets back to push this out to short cover
moves in towards the pad , moves past the waft, and rolls away off the pad to the off side
short of length, shapes to pull but is beaten by the lack of bounce and ends up jabbing it to the on side
stretches well forward, bat and pad close together as he defends
gets forward to work this full-length delivery tailing in on the middle to midwicket
gets on to the front foot and drives to mid-off
angling away from a short of length, goes for the cut but ends up mistiming it on this slow pitch
And again. This time the ball rolls back down the track from the inner half of the bat
on the pads, tucked behind square-leg
short in length outside off, this time Jamie connects with the cut but can't beat the off-side field
gets forward to push towards mid-off for a quick single
goes for the pull of the front-foot and drags the ball to deep backward square-leg region
full in length, straightening outside off, pushed to mid-off
moves in towards off and middle, tapped to short midwicket
Huge! What a strike. He leaned forward, cleared the front foot and knifed through the line. Up and over long-on
on the middle and leg line, flicked away to short midwicket.
Wallop! Guptill is on the bike. Slightly short and he swivels ever so quickly to crash-pull it over midwicket boudnary
Jamie joins in with an elegant off drive. He glided forward to drive it between the bowler and mid-off
Hello Hello! Jamie pings deep midwicket boundary. He walked down the track, collected the short ball and deposited it over midwicket with a fierce pull
short in length, on the middle and off, stabbed to the on side
shortish, outside off, angling away, Jamie goes for the pull but ends up pushing the ball towards mid-on
slower one, on the middle, tapped to square-leg for a single
slower one, turned down to fine-leg region
full and outside off, Jamie seemed intent on a big swing but sort of checked his shot there I reckon. The ball rushes past the edge
on the off stump line, defended back to the bowler
lovely delivery in the corridor outside off, from a good length, Jamie is beaten, pushing inside the line
just outside off, again on a good length, pushed down to mid-off
again spot on with the line and length- on the off stump and from a good length, defended to the on side. Leg slip still in.

good delivery actually but very skillfully played. It landed on a good length and straightened on the middle, hoping for a lbw. Jamie leaned forward, ensured that the front leg didn't get in the way and on drove it to the right of mid-on. Nice timing.
goes for the big pull but fails to connect with the short delivery. Kamran collects outside off
slower one, full in length, Guptill waits before guiding it to backward point region
shout for lbw but it looked as if going down the leg side. It was full and Jamie fell over a touch on that front foot and played all around it. It had landed outside leg as well

A slower one and short in length as well. Jamie sees the length and goes for the pull but is done in by the lack of pace. He holes out to deep midwicket. Pakistan fielders erupt in joy, Jamie looks back ruefully as he trudges off
gets behind the line of the good-length delivery and pushes it back to the bowler
on the middle, tapped to the on side
short in length, straightens on the middle stump line, defended to the on side
just outside off stump, defended to the off side of the pitch and Sohail moves across to cut it off
nudges this wide of midwicket for a single
Slice of life! He leans forward to slice the full delivery up and over the off-side field to the cover boundary
straightens on the off and middle line, full in length, driven to mid-off
Violent thump! It was a full-length delivery around the off stump line and Guptill unfurled an imperious whack to wide long-on boundary. He leaned forward and swung it over the on-side field
leans forward to work this to right of mid-on .. It should have been a single but Gul makes a mess of it as he tries to slide and stop
gets forward to push it to midwicket
leans forward to defend the full-length delivery to the leg side
gets forward to work it to right of Gul at mid-on for a single
leans across to steer to point
fuller but down the leg side. Wide
Fine shot this. It was a slower one, full on the legs, Guptill waited for the ball to arrive before he whip-flicks it to the square-leg boundary.
shortish delivery, tapped to square-leg for a single
short in length, straightens on the middle stump line, Guptill stays on the back foot to clip it through  midwicket
full and wider outside off, Guptill goes for the big cover drive but no wood on leather
short in length, Guptill goes for his fav pull but ends up mistiming and edging it to just right of midwicket
slants away from Ross Taylor who is beaten, pushing away from the body, he then practices shouldering arms
fuller, just outside off again, run down to third man
starts off with a wide down the leg side
lands full in length outside off and moves away, left alone
lands full in length and straightens outside off, Taylor leans well forward to defend
shorter in length, Taylor had committed himself on the front foot and went for the cut from there but couldn't beat point

Younis takes a neat catch at first slip. It was a probing delivery that landed on a good length outside off and straightened. Rosco got forward to defend and ended up stabbing it to left of Younis who lunges low to pouch it.
presses back to push it to cover

Loud shout for lbw but it appeared to be missing leg. It was the full delivery from Gull, one of his specialities, Styris got his front leg in the way, removed it and ended up playing around the ball. Howzaat? went the cry.. Looked like it was going down
slower one, tapped close on the off and they rush across
gets back and across to punch it to through point
full and well outside off, Guptill goes for the booming off drive but doesn't quite get across in time and the ball flies past the edge
nice slower one from middle of the pitch, Guptill had gone for the pull, realised the ball was not there, waited and just about managed to lap it around the corner. He smiles later.
probing teasing delivery, going away with the left-armer's angle, Styris is beaten, pushing inside the line
wider outside off and Styris chases it to cut but can't reach
goes back and across to clip this one through midwicket
leans across to square drive this length delivery crisply to left of point where Hafeez makes a fine diving save
fuller, driven but straight to covers. He should have done more with that though, having said that, the off side is packed.
That slow bouncer again! Guptill is early through with his pull shot and the ball moves past the bat and bounces once before it reaches Akmal, who is hit on the left knee
sprays this wide down the leg side
just outside the off stump, chopped to gully region for a single
in the zone outside off, holding its line, Styris is beaten, driving inside the line
dabs this to the midwicket region
stays back to tap this to the on side
shortish, again slow in pace, Styris edges the pull shot to backward square-leg
slower one again, cuts in from around the off stump, on the middle stump line, nudged behind square-leg. Lovely slower one that. It cut back in

A chance? fuller and wider outside off, Styris goes after it and ends up slashing it towards thirdman .. where Sohail Tanveer is late in picking the ball. He reacts late, moves forward and even throws in a dive but can't reach it.
well outside the off stump

Caught  or grounded? is the question. Replays suggest it was a clean catch . Guptill has to go, after he gets confirmation from the third umpire. Guptill  pressed back to punch it away from the body and Shehzad dived forward full towards the ball at point to pouch it. Smart catch. 80 for 3 and NZ are wobbling here. The umpires have told the batsman to wait. They go upstairs. Shehzad dived forward, caught the ball cleanly above the ground and the question is when he landed did the ball touch the ground. But the right palm came under the ball at that point and the ball doesn't seem to have touched the ground. Out!
gets back to defend this back down the track. Free hit coming up
Kaned! he shuffles to the off, clears the front foot and heaves the full delivery to long-on boundary
short in length, straightens outside off, pushed to point
full in length outside off, steered through point
gets back to clip this through midwicket
slower one, full in length outside off, pushed to the off side
full and well outside off, Styris leans across to square drive it to deep point
gets forward to push the good-length delivery to the off side
leans forward to drive to long-off
pushed away to the off side
leans well forward to work this to the on side
turns this to square-leg region
leans forward to push it back down the track
short in length outside off, Styris punches it to deep point
bouncer on the middle and leg line, Kane allows it to fly over his left shoulder. For a moment there, he was thinking about the pull shot but just about pushed his bat down under the ball
full in length, nice delivery, moving in from outside off, Williamson lunges forward to jab it away
straightens on a full length outside off, driven to the off side
leans forward to drive to the on side
slightly slower outside off, pushed out to covers
flighted full just outside off, driven to left of long-off for a single
flighted outside off, slower, Styris is beaten on the attempted square drive
connects this time but can't beat point
slides on to the middle stump, looking for the lbw, eased down to long-on
on the middle stump line, tapped to midwicket
short in length outside off, forced down to sweeper cover
full in length outside off, left alone
short in length around off, punches back down the track, Gul gets a hand on it and the ball rolls to the stumps but Styris had lunged back to get inside the crease
punches this to extra cover
leans forward to drive straight to mid-on
gets forward to punch it to left of mid-on
lands full in length and straightens outside off, squeezed out to the point region
flighted delivery full in length around off, turns away, driven to left of long-off
spins away from the off, square driven through cover point
presses back to force this to deep cover
on the off stump line, a touch quicker, pushed to covers
slower, on the off stump line, swatted away to midwicket
from a round-armish action, well outside off, turns away, Styris chases it and gets a bottom-edge and the ball bounces enroute to Kamran
short in length just outside off, punched to left of mid-off
wide outside off stump, Styris chases it but can't connect.
gets on the front foot and chops the length delivery to point
moves towards the pads, rolls away to the off and they rush across for the quick single
keeps low after landing on a good length around off, pushed to mid-off for a single.. over throws
pushes this to mid-on for a single
turns away with bounce and Styris is beaten, as he attempts to cut it
fuller and on the pads, flicked to short fine-leg region. Razzaq with the throw but he needed a direct hit to run out Kane, who dived to get back
rocks back to cut to point
glides forward to drive through extra cover
that loopy delivery from a round-armish release, full and outside off, driven to sweeper cover
backs away to drag this delivery from the off and middle line to deep midwicket
full in length outside off, driven to deep point
on the off stump line, pushed out to the off
Edged to third man boundary. It was the full length delivery outside off and Styris tried to drive it square of the wicket off the front foot and got a fat edge
cuts in with bounce and Styris is in trouble. He didn't expect the movement nor the bounce and tried to jab it away but is hit on the thigh
full in length, moves in towards middle, worked to midwicket
around the off stump line, steered through backward point

turns away from Styris who taps it to right  of backward point where Tanvir makes a mess of a regulation stop. And he gives away an extra run. Afridi has a quizzical look on his face as he stares at Sohail
gets forward to dab it wide of midwicket
leans forward to drive to long-off
leans across to ping Umar Akmal at sweeper cover
turns this past square-leg
just outside off, shjort in length, cut to left of point where Shezad makes a fine save
flighted on a good length outside off, eased to long-on
fuller, around off, worked around to short midwicket
gets down the track and drives to the bowler
moves down the track and lofts it to right of long-on for couple of runs
rocks back to cut it to sweeper cover for couple more
Neat. He leans forward to drive to left of long-off this time and will pick up two more
smacked through point into the deep for a single
short of a good length outside off, rocks back and slaps it towards deep cover for a single
quicker through the air, turns away, pushes through the line and gets a thick outside edge, short third man does well to stop it
fullish on the off, pushed back to the bowler
another dot, pitched up on the off, played back to the bowler
floating it full on middle, dug out into the leg side towards midwicket, one more
tossed up, Williamson comes down the track and drags it wide of long-on for a couple
short ball on middle, pulled away to deep square leg
played across the line there did Styris, got an inside edge onto the pads, was looking to fetch it from outside off
on middle and leg, pushed down the ground to long-on for a single
slightly short on the off, turning in, worked away through square leg for a single
pitched up on the off, driven slightly uppishly but wide of midwicket for a brace
full toss on the off, punched down the ground to long-off
looping it towards middle and getting it to turn, Styris plays against the spin and gets a leading edge past cover for a single
short ball outsid eoff, slapped past cover
goodish length on the off, defended towards point
opened the face slightly to tap it towards point
three dots in a row, short and wide, goes for the cut but isn't able to connect
pushed back past the bowler
driven down the ground towards long-on
slightly short on middle, worked away off the back foot through square leg
goodish length on middle, pushed back to the bowler
turning in, tickled towards short fine but it's a wayward throw from Tanvir that allows him to complete the single
short delivery, pulled away to deep backward square-leg
a long hop  outside off now, also keeps low, dragged down to deep midwicket
another short delivery, turns away from the off this time, Styris swipes it across the line to wide long-on region
quicker! medium pace this time... seam-up and it tilts in from outside off, Styris is beaten
slower, cut away to deep point
Whoa! This one is slower and breaks away sharply, A mystified Kane is beaten, stabbing inside the line. A wide variety of deliveries in that over!
moves down the track to ping long-on
pauses just before release and floats it outside off, punched away neatly to right of deep cover where Younis khan makes a fine diving save.
flighted delivery on the middle and off line on a good length, Kane moved down the track and drove it back down the pitch
works this past square-leg for a single
around the off stump line, tapped around to midwicket
turns to the middle stump line. pushed down the track, the bowler moves to his right, behind the non striker and stops it
leans forward to tap this to midwicket

backs away a touch and goes for the lofted shot down the ground but miscues it. Catch it was the cry but it doesn't reach Wahab who moved in from long-on. He was late to react and didn't advance quickly forward.
pulled away to Hafeez at midwicket , throw at the non-striker's end but fails to find the stumps. Styris was outside the crease; had it been a direct hit ...
punched away to the off for a single

Another run out chance missed. It was that lovely slower one that lands on a good length and cuts back in Styris who tapped towards backward point and rushed across. Shehzad had all the time in the world to take aim and shoot but he misses. Kane was not even in the frame.
leans forward to drive to the mid-off

Nice catch from Umar Akmal. Is that the game-breaking blow? Styris connected with the slog sweep and the white ball seemed to be soaring over midwicket boundary. Umar stationed himself just inside the boundary, hopped back to reach above him and plucked it. He then looks back to see whether his feet are safe inside the line. They are. Out!
goes down the track and dabs to midwicket
presses back to work it to square-leg
stays back to chip it uppishly but well short of the bowler
gets forward to tap it to left of covers for a single
goes down the track to heave to the on side but is beaten in flight and ends up edging it in the air but short of backward point
leans forward to defend bat and pad  to the off side
goes down the track but is beaten by the lack of pace. He tried to whip the leg-side delivery to the on side and the ball rolls off the pad
loopy slower one, full on the pads, tucked past square-leg
slower one, outside off, angling away, punched to right of sweeper cover
Whack. He picked the slower one early, waited for it on the front foot and lofted it to the straight boundary
full in length, on the middle, tapped to right of midwicket for a single
Dropped by Afridi It was a full toss and Brendon chipped it to left of Afridi who lunged sideways with both hands but spilled the ball
stays back to steer this to backward point
gets forward to drive to short extra cover
quicker one, gets forward to push it to extra cover
slower, Kane comes down the track, takes it on the full and drives to sweeper cover
quicker one, Brendon goes back to steer it through covers
sprays this wide down the leg side and Kamran dives but he can't reach it
advances down the track, gets outside leg in the process and slaps a short-of-length delivery to backward point where its smartly fielded
Castled! It was the slower one, on the middle, from a back of length, Kane had to wait on that front foot, he then tried to swat it across the line but edged it back on to his stumps
in the corridor and Oram lets it fly through to Kamran
in the zone outside off, left alone
full in length outside off, steered to third man
slower one outside off, Brendon adjusts at the last minute to tap it to the off side
full in length, straightens just outside off, pushed through covers

Brendon is run out It was pushed to right of backward point and they went for the risky single. Direct hit has Brendon out by a meter.. Umar Akmal is thrilled as he dashes off towards his team-mates. Brendon is pretty angry and upset as he storms off
short in length, just outside leg and straightens to hit the pad.
gets back to punch it through covers
in the zone outside off, left alone
gets across to defend to the off side
banged in short outside off stump line, chopped away to point region
gets forward to punch it to deep point

Dropped by Younis It kicked up from short of length outside off and Oram went for the on the up punch and the ball flew well to left of Younis who dives to his left but can't hold on to the tough chance
stays back to steer this to backward point
slower one, almost drops in on the blockhole, dug out to point
another slower one, on the pads, rolls away to the leg side
gets forward to jab this one to the leg side
lands on a good length on the middle and straightens, Woodcock taps it to the off side
full and outside the leg stump. Shout for lbw but that landed outside the leg stump. Woodcock played all around it
Run out chance missed by Umar Akmal . Woodcock steered it to backward point and ran across. Umar dived to his left, stopped it, got up, took aim and fired. But missed it. Oram had given up the ghost.
the surprise bouncer arrives and Oram fend it away in the air; the ball pops up on the off side but falls well short of any fielders
fuller in length, around off, Oram shuffles across to defend
slower one, wide outside off, Woodcock reaches out to tap it to extra cover
leans forward to drive to long-on
full delivery well outside the off stump, Woodcock reaches out and tries to squeeze it to point but doesn't connect
yet another one of those back-of-hand slower ones, Woodcock has a swing across the line but makes no contact
leans forward to drive to mid-off
goes across the line to deep square-leg region. He took the bottom hand off the handle and swung across
gets forward to on drive this for couple of runs
this one breaks away from Oram, from leg to middle, stabbed to backward point
around the off stump, steered to backward point
Massive! Oram rushed down the track and smashed this into the stands beyond long-on. Afridi scratches his forehead.
slower, lands outside leg and breaks in towards leg, flicked away to deep square-leg region
gets forward to drive to long-off
full and outside off stump, tries to slash it behind point but no contact
flat-bats this good-length delivery to left of mid-off. He didn't connect well
full toss outside off and Woodcock punches it square of the wicket and well to the left of backward point
slower one, on a good length outside off, pushed out weakly to covers

It was full and on the legs, Oram goes for the swat-flick and it balloons down to deep backward square-leg where Hafeez ran in and lunged forward to take it. The catching has been good today. Pakistan inch close
from round the stumps now, goes for the yorker but fires it down the leg side
pushes this behind square-leg for a single
backs away outside leg and crashes this full toss to point where Shehzad lunges over the ball and makes a mess of it.
moves outside leg again, Gul goes for the good-length delivery this time and the ball kicks over the flashing blade
again gets outside leg, Gul slips in a slower one outside off and Mills edges his intended big hit to short fine-leg region. Gul smiles.
Yorked! Thanks for coming. A Gul special. Woodcock tried to bring bat down in a hurry to get some wood on leather but couldn't do it in time. Clatter! The middle stump tilts back
nudges this to the on side for a single
full delivery, pushed out to the off for a single
A nice slower one on the middle, Mills goes for a big swing and misses. The ball bounces over the middle stump
Again that slower one has Mills in a chaotic world. He goes for the big hit, tries to check but the ball floats past the off stump

run out missed by Kamran. It was the yorker length from round the stumps. .. jabbed behind the wicekt and he takes a few steps down the track. Kamran stops and under-arms the throw but misses the stumps
leans forward to drive through mid-off
full delivery, pushed out to mid-off
charges down the track for the wild slog. It's a slower one. The bat completes the swing and the ball arrives late and gently winks past the batsman
More swing and misses. ANother slower one, another big slog across the line and again the ball wobbles to Kamran
the yorker comes in this time, stabbed behind square-leg

slower one and  yorker done and so Umar Gul goes for the bouncer. Pinged on the helmet. Ouch. Mills backed away and went for a weak pull. The ball flew past the bat and crashed into the side of the helmet.
gets forward and drags it through midwicket
Crack. He moves outside leg and smashes this overpitched delivery to the long-off boundary.
goes past the bat swing and Kamran collects
quickish but slips down the leg side for a wide
turns away from the off stump, Southee went for the slog but didn't connect
goes for another slog and misses again.. the ball rolls of the pad
drags this full delivery down to long-on
slower, turns away from the off stump, Mills tries to punch it through the off but makes no contact
backs away to punch to left of Afridi who makes a lunging stop
Nine down. It was slower and flighted up, Mills ended up miscuing it high in the air and long-off moves into the 30-yard circle to take it. Pakistan on the verge
That was interesting! He shuffled outside off, Gull followed him with a full slower one and Southee flicked it and almost on to his stumps! it rolls past and down to fine-leg
moves outside leg and ends up jabbing the yorker to the off side
banged in short outside off, from round the stumps, steered down to third man
gets outside leg, then reaches across to slash it down to third man
low dipping yorker, pushed out to the off
backs away from the leg stump, the ball is full and slants past the bat to Kamran
Ooh .. it missed the off stump but not by much. Again, the same routine from the batsman - move to the leg and swing in hope
yorker on the middle, the batsman moved outside leg and managed to slice it to third man
full delivery on the pads, rolls away to third man .. shout for lbw but that was going down the leg
Yet another one of those swing and misses. Kamran collects again.
from round the stumps, full toss outside off but the batsman was well away from the leg stump and couldn't reach
carves this to deep backward point for a single
low dipping full toss, swung away to deep midwicket
almost caught by Umar Akmal. It was a full toss, flat batted towardds long-on where Umar rushed forward and threw in a brave dive but couldn't get his palms under the ball
leans forward to drive to the mid-on region
moves down the track and drives to long-off
moves outside leg and heaves this leg break over the midwicket boundary where its caught by a fan, who pockets the ball!
